{
  "texts": [
    "The raw features for a node are a tuple (site_id, sum_click, date).",
    "Evaluation metrics: Predicting academic performance is framed as a binary classification task.",
    "The metrics employed for evaluating performance are • Classification Accuracy (ACC): ACC = TP + TN TP + FP + FN + TN, where TP, FP, FN, and TN denote the count of True-Positive, False-Positive, False-Negative, and True-Negative instances in the confusion matrix.",
    "• F1-score (F1): F1 = 2 * REL * PRE REL + PRE,Table 2 Online learning activities used to construct interaction-based graphs Activities Descriptions Homepage Interactions with course main page Subpage Interactions with other embedded sites in course Url Interactions with audio/video content links Forumng Interactions with discussion forum Oucontent Interactions with assignment content Resource Usage of search tool Quiz Interactions with course quiz Table 3 Attributes for constructing attribute-based graphs [15] Attribute Description Highest_education Education level of student at the start of module presentation age_band Student's age group Studied_credits Total credits for modules student is studying Disability Declaration of disability by student Final_result Outcome of student's module presentation Gender Gender of student Region Geographic area of the student during module presentation Num_of_prev_attempts Attempts at this module by student Resource Interactions with course resources Oucontent Interactions with assignment content Homepage Interactions with the main page of course Subpage Interactions with other enabled sites in course Url Interactions with audio/video content links Page Interactions with course information Quiz Interactions with course quiz Forumng Interactions with discussion forum Oucollaborate Interactions with online video discussionswhere F1 is the harmonic mean of REL (REL = TP / (TP + FN)) and PRE (Precision, defined as the proportion of true positives among predicted positives).",
    "Results and discussion Predicting academic performance with complete online learning logsThe first experiment aims to answer the research question: Can our APP-DGNN outperform non-graph-based and graph-based models in predicting student final grades based on their online learning logs?"
  ]
}